content: I've been trying to adopt a more plant-based diet for three months now, and it's been a game-changer for my health and wellbeing. I've been experimenting with different types of protein sources, including tofu, tempeh, and seitan. I recently tried making a vegan "fish" taco using crumbled tofu and a spicy slaw made with red cabbage and carrots, and it was a total hit. I've also been adding protein powder to my smoothies, and I've found that pea protein works really well for me. Anyway, back to protein powder, what are some popular brands that offer high-quality plant-based options?
